# Second Brain — Vault Dashboard

A PARA + Zettelkasten personal knowledge vault, maintained with AI agents.
Scaffolded on {{DATE}} with `npx your-second-mind@latest`.

## Quick start (Day 2+)

```bash
cd {{VAULT_PATH}}
claude   # opens Claude Code with CLAUDE.md loaded
```

Or in Cursor: `cursor {{VAULT_PATH}}`

## Folder overview

| Folder | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `raw/` | Immutable source documents — never modified by agents |
| `00-Inbox/` | Unprocessed captures — triage weekly |
| `10-Daily/` | Daily notes `YYYY-MM-DD.md` |
| `20-Projects/` | Active, time-bound projects |
| `30-Areas/` | Ongoing responsibilities |
| `40-Resources/` | Reference + learning wiki |
| `50-Slipbox/` | Atomic evergreen notes (full-sentence titles) |
| `60-MOCs/` | Maps of Content — hand-curated indexes |
| `70-People/` | CRM-style person notes |
| `80-Archive/` | Inactive / historical — read-only |
| `90-Meta/` | Templates, attachments, AI session logs |

## Agent entry points

- **Claude Code**: reads `CLAUDE.md` at session start
- **Cursor**: reads `.cursorrules` at session start
- **Codex**: reads `AGENTS.md` at session start

Active agents in this vault: {{AGENTS_USED}}

## Key files

- `index.md` — LLM-maintained page catalog; read before any query
- `log.md` — append-only activity record
- `agents-workflow/` — portable agent commands (weekly-review, monthly-lint)

## Common agent prompts

```
Triage my inbox
Ingest raw/<source>/<filename>
Process this week
Find knowledge gaps in <topic>
Generate an MOC for <topic>
Lint the wiki
```

